{"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(_:)-259dx","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(_:)-34tv","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(_:)-98ud2","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(_:)-9tw13","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(_:)-9z2mi","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(object:object:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/init(simple:data:)"]},{"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/ptr"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"title":"Type Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/new(object:object:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/new(simple:data:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Methods"},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/ClosureProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ClosureRef","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It will generally comprise a function of some kind and a marshaller"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"used to call it. It is the responsibility of the marshaller to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"convert the arguments for the invocation from "},{"code":"GValues","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" into","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a suitable form, perform the callback on the converted arguments,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and transform the return value back into a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Value"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the case of C programs, a closure usually just holds a pointer"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to a function and maybe a data argument, and the marshaller"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"converts between ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Value","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and native C types. The GObject","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"library provides the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/CClosure"},{"text":" type for this purpose. Bindings for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other languages need marshallers which convert between "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GValues"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and suitable representations in the runtime of the language in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"order to use functions written in that language as callbacks. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_closure_set_marshal()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to set the marshaller on such a custom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"closure implementation.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Within GObject, closures play an important role in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implementation of signals. When a signal is registered, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"c_marshaller","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" argument to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_signal_new()"},{"text":" specifies the default C","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"marshaller for any closure which is connected to this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"signal. GObject provides a number of C marshallers for this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"purpose, see the g_cclosure_marshal_"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"() functions. Additional C"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"marshallers can be generated with the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"#glib-genmarshal","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"utility.  Closures can be explicitly connected to signals with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_signal_connect_closure()"},{"text":", but it usually more convenient to let","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"GObject create a closure automatically by using one of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"g_signal_connect_"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":"() functions which take a callback function\/user","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"data pair."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using closures has a number of important advantages over a simple","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"callback function\/data pointer combination:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Closures allow the callee to get the types of the callback parameters,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which means that language bindings don’t have to write individual glue"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for each callback type.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The reference counting of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure"},{"type":"text","text":" makes it easy to handle reentrancy"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"right; if a callback is removed while it is being invoked, the closure","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and its parameters won’t be freed until the invocation finishes."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_closure_invalidate()"},{"type":"text","text":" and invalidation notifiers allow callbacks to be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automatically removed when the objects they point to go away.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"code":"GClosure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef"},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GClosure"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef","isActive":true},{"text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GClosure","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/closureref"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"GClosure","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a callback supplied by the programmer."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"]]},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ClosureRef","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject10ClosureRefV","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ClosureRef","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ClosureRef","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Structure","symbolKind":"struct"},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureProtocol","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP"],"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef"},"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ClosureRef/init(_:)-9tw13":{"fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"t